<br>
All of that aside, Lasgalen's sigs are probably no worse than the more extreme ones with women in them.  So asking him to stop using them probably does constitute a form of discrimination I wouldn't support, unless there was a general push to get all the toons better clad for a change.  I mean really, do all the F&amp;F women really raid in their undies?  /sigh<br>
<br>
So I disagree with the idea that Las is worse than anyone else using similar sigs, but I have no desire to flame the initial poster of this thread.  He's aware of the possibility of a double standard and isn't sure of his own reactions and I can respect that.  It's hard to stay even-handed when one thing turns you on and the other just makes you roll your eyes.  I expect women are very familiar with being the ones surrounded by absurd expressions of what men find attractive without any balancing factors at all, so I think noticing what it feels like to be in that position is a healthy thing.<br>
<br>
Yes, it's kind of a dead topic, but that doesn't mean it can't be useful to notice and acknowledge the double standards that exist out there.  That alone is worth a thread or two.  So no flame for posting this.  It was done reasonably enough.<br>
<br>
And yes, for the record, I could do without all the near-pornographic amine.  If/when I want to find it, I know where to get it.  <br>
